# MoonPad — Full Stack Specification (Frontend + Backend + Infrastructure)

## Overview

This document covers everything outside the Anchor smart contract: the Next.js frontend, API backend, database, image/metadata storage, and deployment. Read alongside `anchor-program-spec.md`.

**Live product URL (target):** moonpad.gg (or similar)
**Primary users:** Token creators (devs) and presale participants (degens)

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Frontend | Next.js 14 (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS |
| Wallet | @solana/wallet-adapter-react, Phantom, Backpack, Solflare |
| Anchor client | @coral-xyz/anchor, @solana/web3.js |
| Backend API | Next.js API routes (same repo) |
| Database | PostgreSQL via Supabase (free tier → scale up) |
| ORM | Prisma |
| File storage | Pinata (IPFS) for token images and metadata JSON |
| Event indexing | Custom Helius webhook listener |
| Hosting | Vercel (frontend + API) |
| RPC | Helius (paid) — do NOT use public RPC for production |

