## Transaction UX Patterns

Solana transactions are fast but confirmations still take 1–3 seconds. Use this pattern everywhere:

```typescript
// 1. Optimistic UI: immediately update state before confirmation
// 2. Show spinner with "Confirming..." text
// 3. On confirm: show success toast with explorer link
// 4. On error: show error toast, revert optimistic state

const EXPLORER_BASE = "https://solscan.io/tx";

function explorerLink(sig: string) {
  return `${EXPLORER_BASE}/${sig}`;
}

// Toast example (use react-hot-toast or sonner):
import toast from "react-hot-toast";

toast.promise(
  sendAndConfirm(), // your async fn
  {
    loading: "Confirming transaction...",
    success: (sig) => (
      <span>
        Done!{" "}
        <a href={explorerLink(sig)} target="_blank">
          View on Solscan ↗
        </a>
      </span>
    ),
    error: (e) => `Failed: ${e.message}`,
  }
);
```

