## Launch Sequence (What Happens When User Submits "Launch")

```
1. User fills form → clicks "Connect wallet & pay 1 SOL to launch"
2. Frontend:
   a. POST /api/upload → image to Pinata → get image IPFS URL
   b. POST /api/metadata → metadata JSON to Pinata → get metadata URI
   c. Generate new mint Keypair (client side)
   d. Build initializePresale tx (program.methods.initializePresale...)
   e. partialSign with mint keypair
   f. sendTransaction → user signs in wallet → broadcast
3. await confirmTransaction
4. POST /api/presales with all metadata → write to DB
5. Redirect to /presale/[mint]
6. Helius webhook fires → updates DB with on-chain state
```

---

## Security Notes for Frontend

- Never expose `PINATA_JWT` to the client — all Pinata calls go through `/api/upload` and `/api/metadata`
- Rate-limit API routes: use Vercel's `@vercel/kv` or simple IP-based rate limiting to prevent spam
- Validate all user inputs server-side before writing to DB
- The program is the source of truth — DB is just a read cache for fast queries. Always fetch on-chain state for anything financial
- Do not trust the mint keypair from the client for any API writes — derive presale data from the mint pubkey only after confirming it matches a valid on-chain presale state

